You Can Fix This Easily Using Foobar2000.

First you will need File Integrity Verifier 1.1 from:

http://www.foobar2000.org/components/view/foo_verifier

That is if you wish to verify the problem yourself and wish to verify they are fixed.

Now simply load up all the songs in foobar2000. Select them all, easy enough by clicking on first song in list and then hold down the shift key and click on the last song, that causes all songs to be selected. ctrl+a does not work for me.

Now once you have all songs select you simply need to right click on one of them.

From the context menu mouse over utilities.

For The First One Above Select: Rebuild MP3 Stream

For The Rest Select: Fix VBR MP3 Header

Easy enough, took less than 10 seconds to fix them.

After or before if you wish right click again on one of the songs after selecting them all and this time mouse over Utilities again but choose verify integrity this time.

This will tell you if there are any problems with any of the selected songs.
